  "summary": "Main\nin Weekly Vessel Valuations Report 29/08/2023\nImage reference: 2023-08-29_weekly-vessel-valuations-report-august-29-2023_img1.png\nBulkers : Mid-age Supramax BCs have decreased in response to recent deals. Mid age Capesize have increased owing to strong sale prices of HL Imabari and Santa Lucia Last week. Capesize vessels over 18YO have decreased owing to falling scrap rates (vessels of this age range currently have a higher scrap value than market value, hence scrap value takes precedence)\nCapesize BC Santa Lucia (176,800 DWT, Aug 2006, Namura) sold to Beks Shipmanagement Turkey for USD 16.35 mil, VV Value USD 15.73\nCapesize BC Yuan Fu Star (175,200 DWT, Dec 2011, Jiangsu Rongsheng) sold to unknown Middle Eastern buyers for USD 23 mil, VV Value USD 22.73 mil\nPost Panamax BC AOM Elena (106,500 DWT, Mar 2010, Oshima) sold to unknown Indonesian buyers for USD 20.50 mil, VV Value USD 19.69 mil\nSupramax BC Star Globe (56,900 DWT, May 2010, Taizhou Kouan) sold to undisclosed buyers for USD 11.20 mil, VV Value USD 12.65 mil\nSupramax BC Sky Globe (56,900 DWT, Nov 2009-May 2010, Taizhou Kouan) sold to undisclosed buyers for USD 10.70 mil, VV Value USD 12.28 mil\nTankers : Tanker values ",
